{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "sentry-attendance-collection-v1",
    "name": "SENTRY — Attendance API",
    "description": "Postman collection for the SENTRY Attendance Management System.\n\n## What's in here\n\n1. **FastAPI backend endpoints** — the production REST API documented in the README's Migration section. Use these once your FastAPI backend is running locally or on Render.\n2. **Gemini API call** — the actual external call the single-file app makes from the browser. Test it standalone.\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Open **Variables** (collection-level) and set:\n   - `baseUrl` — your backend URL (default: `http://localhost:8000`)\n   - `geminiKey` — your Gemini API key from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey\n3. Run **Auth → Login** first — the token is auto-saved to `{{token}}` and used by every other authenticated request\n4. Use **Attendance → Punch In** to create a record — its ID auto-saves to `{{attendanceId}}`, then **Overtime → Request** uses it\n\n## Auth model\n\nBearer JWT in `Authorization` header on every authenticated route. Login response saves token automatically via test script.\n\n## Roles\n\n- `employee` — punch in/out, view own data, request overtime\n- `manager` — approve/reject overtime, view team data, AI assistant, reports\n- `admin` — everything above + user management, flag invalid records",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Signup, login, and current-user lookup. Login auto-saves the JWT to `{{token}}`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Signup",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "signup"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Aman Verma\",\n  \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"correcthorsebatterystaple\",\n  \"role\": \"employee\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account.\n\n**Body**\n- `name` (string, required)\n- `email` (string, required, unique)\n- `password` (string, required, min 6 chars)\n- `role` (enum: `employee` | `manager` | `admin`)\n\n**Returns** `{ user, token }` — token is auto-saved by the test script."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('token', data.token);",
                  "  if (data.user?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', data.user.id);",
                  "  pm.test('returns user and token', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('user');",
                  "    pm.expect(data).to.have.property('token');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Aman Verma\",\n  \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"correcthorsebatterystaple\",\n  \"role\": \"employee\"\n}"
                },
                "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup"
              },
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n    \"name\": \"Aman Verma\",\n    \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n    \"role\": \"employee\",\n    \"disabled\": false,\n    \"face_enrolled\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-05-05T10:30:00Z\"\n  },\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n  \"password\": \"correcthorsebatterystaple\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Authenticate and receive a JWT.\n\n**Body**\n- `email` (string, required)\n- `password` (string, required)\n\n**Returns** `{ user, token }` — token is auto-saved to `{{token}}` and used by all subsequent requests."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('token', data.token);",
                  "  if (data.user?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', data.user.id);",
                  "  if (data.user?.role) pm.collectionVariables.set('role', data.user.role);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('login returns 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n    \"name\": \"Aman Verma\",\n    \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n    \"role\": \"employee\",\n    \"disabled\": false,\n    \"face_enrolled\": true\n  },\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Invalid credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"detail\": \"Incorrect email or password\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the currently authenticated user. Use this to verify the JWT is valid."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n  \"name\": \"Aman Verma\",\n  \"email\": \"aman@sentry.dev\",\n  \"role\": \"employee\",\n  \"disabled\": false,\n  \"face_enrolled\": true\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Face Recognition",
      "description": "Face enrollment and verification. Selfies are sent as base64 dataURLs.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Enroll Face",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/face/enroll",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "face", "enroll"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"selfie_base64\": \"data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/...\",\n  \"liveness_verified\": true\n}"
            },
            "description": "Enrolls the current user's face descriptor on the server.\n\n**Body**\n- `selfie_base64` (string, required) — JPEG dataURL\n- `liveness_verified` (bool) — set true if client-side blink detection passed\n\n**Returns** `{ success, descriptor_length }`. Server computes the 128-dim descriptor with `face-recognition` Python lib + OpenCV, stores it on the user record."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"descriptor_length\": 128,\n  \"message\": \"Face enrolled successfully\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 No face detected",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"detail\": \"No face detected in image\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Face",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/face/verify",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "face", "verify"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"selfie_base64\": \"data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/...\",\n  \"liveness_verified\": true\n}"
            },
            "description": "Verify a selfie against the enrolled descriptor. Used internally by punch-in/out, also exposed for direct testing.\n\n**Returns** `{ matched, distance, threshold }`. `matched` is `distance < threshold` (default `0.55`)."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 Match",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"matched\": true,\n  \"distance\": 0.412,\n  \"threshold\": 0.55\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "200 No match",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"matched\": false,\n  \"distance\": 0.781,\n  \"threshold\": 0.55\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Attendance",
      "description": "Punch in / punch out and history queries. Punch endpoints internally call face verification.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Punch In",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/punch-in",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "attendance", "punch-in"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"selfie_base64\": \"data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/...\",\n  \"liveness_verified\": true,\n  \"geo\": {\n    \"lat\": 23.2599,\n    \"lng\": 77.4126,\n    \"accuracy\": 12.5\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Marks the start of an attendance session. Server verifies face → checks geofence (if configured) → creates attendance record.\n\n**Errors**\n- `409` if there's already an open punch for today\n- `403` if face doesn't match\n- `400` if no enrolled descriptor"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('attendanceId', data.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"66a1b2c3d4e5f6789abcdef0\",\n  \"user_id\": \"65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n  \"date\": \"2026-05-05\",\n  \"punch_in\": \"2026-05-05T09:14:23Z\",\n  \"punch_out\": null,\n  \"hours\": 0,\n  \"status\": \"INCOMPLETE\",\n  \"in_geo\": { \"lat\": 23.2599, \"lng\": 77.4126, \"accuracy\": 12.5 },\n  \"face_distance_in\": 0.412,\n  \"in_geofence\": true\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Punch Out",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/punch-out",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "attendance", "punch-out"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"selfie_base64\": \"data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/...\",\n  \"liveness_verified\": true,\n  \"geo\": {\n    \"lat\": 23.2599,\n    \"lng\": 77.4126,\n    \"accuracy\": 8.2\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Closes the open attendance session. Computes hours, classifies status (PRESENT / INCOMPLETE / OT_PENDING).\n\n**Status logic**\n- `< 8h` → INCOMPLETE\n- `8-8.5h` → PRESENT\n- `> 8.5h` → OT_PENDING (employee must request OT)"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"66a1b2c3d4e5f6789abcdef0\",\n  \"date\": \"2026-05-05\",\n  \"punch_in\": \"2026-05-05T09:14:23Z\",\n  \"punch_out\": \"2026-05-05T18:42:11Z\",\n  \"hours\": 9.46,\n  \"status\": \"OT_PENDING\",\n  \"face_distance_out\": 0.398\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "My History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/history?start_date=2026-04-01&end_date=2026-05-05&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "attendance", "history"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "start_date", "value": "2026-04-01" },
                { "key": "end_date", "value": "2026-05-05" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Current user's attendance history within a date range."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Today",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/today",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "attendance", "today"]
            },
            "description": "The current user's record for today, or `null` if not punched in yet."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "All (Manager / Admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/all?date=2026-05-05&user_id=&status=",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "attendance", "all"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "date", "value": "2026-05-05" },
                { "key": "user_id", "value": "" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "All attendance records (admin) or team records (manager). Supports filters: `date`, `user_id`, `status`, `start_date`, `end_date`. Forbidden for `employee`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "403 Forbidden",
              "status": "Forbidden",
              "code": 403,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"detail\": \"Insufficient role: requires manager or admin\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Overtime",
      "description": "Overtime request and approval workflow.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request OT",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/overtime/request",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "overtime", "request"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"attendance_id\": \"{{attendanceId}}\",\n  \"hours_over\": 1.46,\n  \"reason\": \"Client deployment ran past schedule\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Employee submits an overtime request for a record with `OT_PENDING` status. Uses `{{attendanceId}}` from the most recent Punch In response."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (data.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('overtimeId', data.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"66b2c3d4e5f6789abcdef012\",\n  \"user_id\": \"65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1\",\n  \"attendance_id\": \"66a1b2c3d4e5f6789abcdef0\",\n  \"hours_over\": 1.46,\n  \"reason\": \"Client deployment ran past schedule\",\n  \"status\": \"pending\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-05-05T18:43:02Z\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List OT Requests",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/overtime/list?status=pending",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "overtime", "list"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "pending", "description": "pending | approved | rejected | (omit for all)" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List overtime requests. Employees see their own; managers/admins see all."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Decide (Approve / Reject)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/overtime/{{overtimeId}}/decide",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "overtime", "{{overtimeId}}", "decide"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"approved\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Manager/admin only. Approves or rejects a pending OT request. On approval, the linked attendance record's status flips to `OT_APPROVED`. On rejection, it reverts to `PRESENT`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
