    {
      "name": "External — Gemini API",
      "description": "The actual external API call the single-file app makes from the browser. Test it standalone — useful for verifying your `geminiKey` works and for debugging tool-calling prompts.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Generate Content (tool-call style)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/{{model}}:generateContent?key={{geminiKey}}",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["generativelanguage", "googleapis", "com"],
              "path": ["v1beta", "models", "{{model}}:generateContent"],
              "query": [{ "key": "key", "value": "{{geminiKey}}" }]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"contents\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"parts\": [{\n        \"text\": \"You are SENTRY, an attendance analytics assistant.\\n\\nAvailable functions:\\n- get_late_arrivals(date, threshold_hour): list employees who punched in after threshold_hour on date\\n- get_pending_overtime(): list pending OT requests\\n- get_attendance_summary(start_date, end_date): summary stats\\n\\nToday's date is 2026-05-05.\\n\\nTo call a function, respond with ONLY a JSON code block:\\n```json\\n{ \\\"tool\\\": \\\"name\\\", \\\"args\\\": { ... } }\\n```\\n\\nUser question: who came late today\"\n      }]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"generationConfig\": {\n    \"temperature\": 0.3\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Direct Gemini API call. This is exactly what the browser sends in the single-file app.\n\n**Set up first**\n- Variable `geminiKey` — your Gemini API key\n- Variable `model` — `gemini-2.0-flash` (default), `gemini-2.5-flash`, or `gemini-1.5-flash`\n\n**Expected response** — a JSON tool-call block, e.g.:\n```json\n{ \"tool\": \"get_late_arrivals\", \"args\": { \"date\": \"2026-05-05\", \"threshold_hour\": 9 } }\n```\n\nThe app then executes that tool locally and sends a follow-up turn with the result, asking Gemini to format the final answer."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — tool call",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"candidates\": [\n    {\n      \"content\": {\n        \"parts\": [\n          {\n            \"text\": \"```json\\n{ \\\"tool\\\": \\\"get_late_arrivals\\\", \\\"args\\\": { \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-05-05\\\", \\\"threshold_hour\\\": 9 } }\\n```\"\n          }\n        ],\n        \"role\": \"model\"\n      },\n      \"finishReason\": \"STOP\",\n      \"index\": 0\n    }\n  ],\n  \"usageMetadata\": {\n    \"promptTokenCount\": 187,\n    \"candidatesTokenCount\": 42,\n    \"totalTokenCount\": 229\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
